3. Explain the difference between centralized and distributed AAA deployment models by describing how each would work in a scenario where multiple Flipkart warehouses need secure network access.
=>Centralized AAA: All warehouses  forward authentication requests to a single central AAA server. A warehouse worker logs in → request goes to HQ server → policy applied uniformly. This ensures consistent security rules but may introduce latency for remote sites.
Distributed AAA: Each warehouse has local AAA servers (with periodic sync to central). Local auth happens quickly on-site for inventory system access. Better for low-latency but requires effort to keep policies synchronized across locations.

4. Pick any one AAA deployment model and list three advantages and two disadvantages of using it for a large-scale app like BookMyShow.
=>Advantages:

Consistent policy enforcement (same login rules for users across cities).
Simplified management and easier auditing of all events from one place.
Stronger central control over sensitive ticketing data.

Disadvantages:

Single point of failure (server outage affects nationwide logins during peak shows).
Potential higher latency for users in remote areas.
